---
title: Notes on whole-sentence G2P thing
---

The papers on Sardin give a good overview of the sort of things required by
a whole text processing pipeline for speech.

[Chat](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-p-684dc8075e508191ae070a06c599469d-current-things-14-june-2025/c/68cd90fd-c3bc-8323-9230-5454beb1bf5e) --- contains my notes

In addition, there's:
- [DeepPhonemizer](https://github.com/spring-media/DeepPhonemizer)
  - Based on [@yolchuyeva19_interspeech] and [@7178767]
  - Good for a baseline for the multilingual G2P paper
- [SoundChoice](https://www.isca-archive.org/interspeech_2022/ploujnikov22_interspeech.html)
  - [chat](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-p-684dc8075e508191ae070a06c599469d/c/68ab421b-66b4-832c-8ebf-e410a01064b2)
  - whole sentence
  - Speechbrain people
  - [dataset](https://huggingface.co/datasets/flexthink/librig2p-nostress-space)
  - based on [this](https://github.com/CorentinJ/librispeech-alignments)
- [WEB-derived pronunciations](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/4960577) [@4960577]
- [Mining Large-Scale Low-Resource Pronunciation Data From Wikipedia](https://arxiv.org/abs/2101.11575)

